Southwest Airlines and Disney have very different cultures, yet both are successful. Southwest and Disney both value customer service. Southwest's courteous flight attendants and Disney theme parks' "Disney enchantment" emphasize customer service. Both firms value teamwork. Southwest encourages staff to collaborate to provide passengers a smooth flight. Disney's "cast members" collaborate to provide visitors a memorable experience. Their innovation cultures vary greatly. Southwest is recognized for adapting rapidly to market shifts and taking strategic risks to remain ahead. Disney emphasizes brand tradition and "history." Communication differs across cultures. Southwest encourages open communication with workers. Disney has a hierarchical culture where senior management communicates with workers. Southwest Airlines and Disney have distinct cultures that have helped them succeed. They have certain similarities, but their approaches to innovation, communication, and legacy reflect their varied business strategies and goals. 